title>   Re: re</span><hr size=1> Far Seekers has now done the Halls of Testing entrance two consecutive nights, fighting, pulling, CR'ing, exploring a bit and generally preparing to farm our SS armor in earnest. In no way do I claim to be some kind of expert on this setting, I'm merely here to ask a favor and to motivate the why of this.<br>
<br>
During the time we've spent here we've also had the opportunity to be wiped by the hub mobs and thereby to form our own opinion on the matter at hand. We have seen the draggro death, the kos person death, the pot death and the open door death. Now the first two produce a predictable result, the person aggroing the hub mobs wether by dragging or simply being kos dies along with those who assist him. These two are fairly easy to get around and thusly they do not present much of a problem.<br>
<br>
The two latter situations produce a wipe. Mobs don't simply attack the persons very obviously on the aggro list but also others and it becomes necessary to CR. Pot death occurs when one of the larger mobs in HoT like an ancient guardian gets potted by the door to HoT. I am aware that ToV AE's adhere to line of sight for their hits but I am at the same time aware of the flimsiness of VI's concept of a wall. I do not know how the walls are defined in code but I've been &quot;inside&quot; walls able to look out on the other side with an unconstricted view, I've gone through walls and I've aggroed things through walls and ceilings. I have of course seen various npc's inside of walls too or just partly sticking out and it is my belief that when the large mobs in HoT are potted they are partly outside VI's definition of a wall, which in this case constitutes the barrier between HoT and the hub, and as such their AE can hit the hub mobs. This is also easy to avoid and in the end it produces a much better result for us to fight the mob somewhere else.<br>
<br>
What I can't personally control however is the HoT door. The custom of asking the guild camping the entrance has been the means of control thus far but it seems to be slowly fraying at the edges from the discussions here at the RTA. Milambus has already touched on the subject; with the door open you enable line of sight (note that the mob is not inside the wall in this case but simply in line of sight) and thereby an AE hitting hub mobs. Doors don't prevent AE's? Having stood outside of Dozekars room a couple of times while fights have been going on inside I disagree. Having fought an AE mob in the middle of the floor directly in front of the HoT door without the hub mobs rushing in on us I disagree.<br>
<br>
With the HoT door open I've experienced too many irregularities for me to believe it's an entirely unimportant matter. Aggro that I cannot explain bothers me and until I can explain it and can find a way to avoid the, according to me, door induced wipes I'd prefer it if the door was kept closed when we have a mob in camp. All of Noble Blade, Tindi Losi and Shadows of Yamabushi can line up and call me superstitious, foolish or some such but I ask you to please respect this when Far Seekers are in the HoT entrance camp. Send me or another raidleader a tell, if a mob is presently in camp it will be a matter of minutes until I or they happily send a tell back saying that the door is safe and you can swish right by. Heh, just humour us and respect our folly and whatnot, it would mean alot to us and we'd of course respond in kind. You are after all making an alteration in our raiding environment <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Kamlatir<br>
Far Seekers  <p><html>
