<br>
The best thing to do, from my experience (quite a few HoT nights ~.~), is to move in. Yes, this means coffin in the case of a wipeout.. but it's usually better than getting random wipeouts due to dumbasses dragging corpses or walling mobs into the assist range of hub mobs.  It also means less issues when other people come in to also raid HoT or kill Doze, etc.  Especially these days when there is literally 10 or 15 HoT-capable and motivated guilds. (It CAN be shared easily by 2 small (18-40) raid parties)<br>
<br>
As for the door, if you worry about it.. do you worry about the anti-camp code too?<br>
